title: The Queen's Gambit - The Final Game (Piano Cover)
description:
This scene!!! The definition of 'satisfaction' when watching it for the first time. The show is really something else. Beth's arc is very well constructed and you really feel happy for her when she sees the chess board on the ceiling during that final game, without the alcohol or drugs. It was in her all this time and she fought for it. Can't wait to rewatch this show over and over again. 
My right wrist and pinky hurt now so I'm gonna do an easier arrangement for the next video. I'd like to do the last piece we hear, Sygrayem (Let's Play). It is so uplifting and so fitting for the ending. 
I also decided to cut away the first 2min of The Final game because I felt it was not part of the thrill of the overall piece. I couldn't remember the melody so I felt it was right to cut it off and start to play when they resume the game.
I do all my arrangements by ear so no sheets.
Thanks a lot for watching!!!
